. The obtained ice Ic shows remarkable thermal stability until the phase\ntransition to ice Ih at 250 K; this thermal stability originates from the lack\nof dislocations, which promote changes in the stacking sequence. This discovery\nof ideal ice Ic will promote understanding of the role of stacking-disorder on\nthe physical properties of ice as a counter end-member of ice Ih.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 8 Sep 2019 07:40:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-19"}
